GIT

Git is a free and open source version control software that is widely used in software development. 
Git allows multiple developers to work on one project by working on their own parts of the project while maintaining a order. GitHub.com is a website that is commonly used that incorporates Git. In GitHub, you can create repositories, which are projects where team member can pull and push code from. 

To get started with Git, you can download it here: https://git-scm.com/downloads 

Here is useful website to help you get started: https://help.github.com/articles/set-up-git/